FBIS4-33614 "drlat111_a_94007" FBIS-LAT-94-111 Daily Report 8 Jun 1994 CARIBBEAN Cuba Oil Companies Discover Cardenas Bay Deposit Oil Companies Discover Cardenas Bay Deposit FL0806174994 Havana Radio Progreso Network in Spanish 1100 GMT 8 Jun 94 FL0806174994 Havana Radio Progreso Network Spanish BFN [From the "First Thing" program] [Text] The first well drilled by oil companies working with Cupet [expansion unknown] in the search for new deposits has yielded positive results. A deposit has been discovered with research currently underway to determine its dimensions. GRANMA reports that the discovery was made at Cardenas Bay, Matanzas Province, in the area leased by Canadian companies Canada Northwest Energy and Fortuna Petroleum, Inc. Tests reveal an estimated daily production of 3,750 barrels of 16 API -- the international unit to measure the oil's density -- oil. The oil is considered heavy but of better quality than the oil extracted at Varadero.
